// @emit-error closure ref-list result element twin
// A LAMBDA whose result is a ref-list of a NULLABLE struct with a CLOSURE field
// (`() => ({f: () => string} | null)[]`): the lambda self-infers a NON-null element
// (`#anon` struct, no `| null`) and interns a `>r<nonNullSlot>;` sig, while the binding
// annotation keys the NULLABLE element on a DIFFERENT slot — the two ref-list WRAPPER
// structs are distinct heap types (array elements are invariant), so the value-call
